stylometry: When to play an order has a few factors. Each time when you place and order you incur holding costs and carrying costs. When you dont order a product but produce there is a equipment or setup cost along with a cost incurred when producing. Other factors that you need to consider when ordering is the amount of lead time you have until you order another amount of inventory. Another is how much of your inventory is on demand will influence when to place an order. Another is will you have enough safety stock to cover demand if your initial inventory runs out
